uring Summer (39%) and gradually decreases through Autumn and Spring, reaching the lowest in Winter (33%).\n","\n","* This indicates that while summer is the peak season for bookings, it also experiences the highest rate of cancellations. Winter, having the fewest bookings, also has the lowest rate of cancellations."],"metadata":{"id":"tlPXgGm5vd2D"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### **Conclusion:**"],"metadata":{"id":"nsAZRAqQwDf0"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**1. High Booking and High Cancellation in Summer:**\n","\n","* Summer is a popular season for hotel bookings, but it also shows the highest cancellation rate. This could be due to factors like overbooking, changes in travel plans, or fluctuations in pricing that cause guests to cancel.\n","\n","**2. Low Booking and Low Cancellation in Winter:**\n","\n","* Winter has the lowest booking volume and also the lowest cancellation rate. This may suggest that people who book during the winter are more committed to their plans, possibly due to specific events or activities like winter sports or holiday gatherings.\n","\n","**3. Potential Strategies:**\n","\n","* Hotels could consider more flexible booking policies, targeted promotions, or pricing strategies to reduce cancellations during the high-demand summer months.\n","\n","* During the winter, hotels may want to focus on special events, discounts, or package deals to boost occupancy rates."],"metadata":{"id":"wyHT55AhwZ1p"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## How do different customer types (e.g., transient, group) affect the average daily rate or likelihood of cancellation?"],"metadata":{"id":"BTM7wBnD70PL"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Group by customer type and calculate mean ADR and cancellation rate\n","customer_type_adr = df.groupby('customer_type')['adr'].mean().reset_index()\n","customer_type_cancellation = df.groupby('customer_type')['is_canceled'].mean().reset_index()\n","\n","# Plot the Average Daily Rate (ADR) by customer type\n"